    "description": "\n    <div class=\"mountain-description prose prose-stone max-w-none\">\n        <p class=\"text-lg text-stone-700 leading-relaxed mb-6\">Rising to 274 feet, Jordan Pond offers one of Maine's finest hiking experiences. \n        Whether you're seeking panoramic views, a family-friendly outing, or a quick escape into nature, \n        this peak delivers.</p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8 mb-4\">Popular Routes</h2>\n        <p class=\"text-stone-600 leading-relaxed mb-4\">The most popular route, **Jordan Pond Path**, covers 3.3 miles and is rated \n    Easy. Easy loop around crystal-clear pond with views of The Bubbles.</p>\n\n        <h2 class=\"text-xl font-bold text-stone-900 mt-8 mb-4\">Peak Bagging</h2>\n        <div class=\"bg-emerald-50 border border-emerald-100 p-4 rounded-xl\">\n            <p class=\"text-emerald-800\">**Extend Your Adventure:** Penobscot Mountain lies just 0.6 \n        miles away, making it an excellent addition for ambitious hikers looking to bag multiple summits.</p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    ",
